The paper deals with the issue of verifying the consistency of replicated data in a distributed network, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a quantum protocol for this problem, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the size of certificates required for classical certification mechanisms, which is related to data structures (cs.DS).
